1
00:00:00,006 --> 00:00:01,008
- [Instructor] Today, we're going to talk

2
00:00:01,008 --> 00:00:03,005
about functions in JavaScript.

3
00:00:03,005 --> 00:00:05,006
Functions are one of the most important concepts

4
00:00:05,006 --> 00:00:06,006
in programming.

5
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:09,000
They allow us to group a set of instructions

6
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,002
into a single unit that can be executed whenever we need it.

7
00:00:13,002 --> 00:00:14,007
Think of a function as a blueprint

8
00:00:14,007 --> 00:00:17,000
for a home improvement project.

9
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,004
The blueprint contains all the instructions

10
00:00:19,004 --> 00:00:21,001
and measurements you need to follow

11
00:00:21,001 --> 00:00:23,000
to complete the project.

12
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,004
Instead of figuring out the steps and measurements

13
00:00:25,004 --> 00:00:27,009
every time you want to do a similar project,

14
00:00:27,009 --> 00:00:30,000
you just refer to the blueprint.

15
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,006
Similarly, instead of writing the same code multiple times,

16
00:00:33,006 --> 00:00:35,006
you write a function and call it whenever you need

17
00:00:35,006 --> 00:00:40,000
to perform a similar task in your program.


18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Here in our script.js file,

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,002
we're going to create a new function called dragElement.

20
00:00:46,002 --> 00:00:50,002
This function will take an HTML element as an argument,

21
00:00:50,002 --> 00:00:53,003
which is defined as terrariumElement here.

22
00:00:53,003 --> 00:00:55,002
This function that I just created here

23
00:00:55,002 --> 00:00:57,008
will take an HTML element as an argument

24
00:00:57,008 --> 00:01:00,000
and make it draggable.

25
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,002
The "function" keyword

26
00:01:01,002 --> 00:01:04,001
is used to declare a function in JavaScript.

27
00:01:04,001 --> 00:01:06,009
The name of our function is dragElement,

28
00:01:06,009 --> 00:01:10,007
and it takes one parameter called terrariumElement.


29
00:01:10,007 --> 00:01:13,006
This parameter represents the HTML element

30
00:01:13,006 --> 00:01:15,009
that we want to make draggable.

31
00:01:15,009 --> 00:01:17,007
Inside the function,

32
00:01:17,007 --> 00:01:20,006
we're going to copy the code that we have on line 1,

33
00:01:20,006 --> 00:01:24,009
and paste it into the body of this function

34
00:01:24,009 --> 00:01:28,001
between the curly braces.

35
00:01:28,001 --> 00:01:31,006
We've moved our position variables inside of the function

36
00:01:31,006 --> 00:01:33,006
to ensure that they are scoped correctly

37
00:01:33,006 --> 00:01:34,007
within the function.

38
00:01:34,007 --> 00:01:35,009
This is going to be important

39
00:01:35,009 --> 00:01:38,003
for tracking the position of the element

40
00:01:38,003 --> 00:01:41,004
during the drag operation.


41
00:01:41,004 --> 00:01:43,001
In this case, the element

42
00:01:43,001 --> 00:01:46,003
that we're going to be dragging are the plants.

43
00:01:46,003 --> 00:01:50,007
So essentially, the terrariumElement parameter here

44
00:01:50,007 --> 00:01:53,004
will be the particular plant

45
00:01:53,004 --> 00:01:57,001
that we will be clicking on and dragging.

46
00:01:57,001 --> 00:01:58,009
And that's it for functions,

47
00:01:58,009 --> 00:02:01,003
which allow us to group a set of instructions

48
00:02:01,003 --> 00:02:02,007
into a single unit

49
00:02:02,007 --> 00:02:05,007
that can be executed whenever we need it.

50
00:02:05,007 --> 00:02:07,007
We created a function called dragElement

51
00:02:07,007 --> 00:02:09,000
that will eventually handle

52
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,008
the dragging of our terrariumElements.


53
00:02:11,008 --> 00:02:13,007
Understanding functions is crucial

54
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:15,003
because they help us organize our code

55
00:02:15,003 --> 00:02:17,008
and make it more reusable.

56
00:02:17,008 --> 00:02:19,000
In the next lesson,

57
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,006
we'll learn about the document object model,

58
00:02:21,006 --> 00:02:23,002
also known as a DOM.

59
00:02:23,002 --> 00:02:25,001
We'll learn about what it is,

60
00:02:25,001 --> 00:02:27,002
and how to manipulate it using JavaScript.

61
00:02:27,002 --> 00:02:37,002
See you soon.

